excerpt: Seafood-focused menu with a local twist by a renowned chef, in an upscale hotel restaurant.
detail_description: Dune is an upscale restaurant located at The Ocean Club, A Four Seasons Resort on Paradise Island. It offers a seafood-focused menu with a local twist, crafted by renowned chef Jean-Georges Vongerichten. The restaurant's British colonial-style setting on Cabbage Beach provides stunning ocean views and a menu that combines local ingredients with French and Asian culinary influences.
name: Dune
address: Paradise Island, One Ocean Drive, Nassau, Bahamas

detail_description: Graycliff Restaurant, located in the renowned Graycliff Hotel, is a celebrated dining destination that has attracted the likes of Beyoncé and Jay-Z. One of its most notable features is the award-winning wine cellar, boasting an impressive collection of 275,000 bottles from 20 different countries. The restaurant offers a sophisticated ambiance with live music and hand-rolled cigars in the lounge before guests move to the garden patio for an exquisite dining experience paired with an extensive selection of wines.
name: Graycliff Restaurant

detail_description: Café Matisse, a Bahamian-style Italian restaurant, is housed in a 19th-century colonial mansion behind Parliament Square. The interior boasts French decor and walls adorned with prints of the eponymous artist. The menu offers modern dishes like veal Calamarata pasta, rack of lamb with mint crust, and mahi-mahi with heirloom vegetables.
name: Café Matisse

detail_description: Café Martinique is a sophisticated dining spot located in the Marina Village at the Atlantis Resort. The restaurant exudes an old-world charm with its vaulted ceilings and soft lighting, offering an intimate and elegant atmosphere. Accessible via a grand staircase or a unique wrought-iron bird-cage elevator, this fine dining establishment by Jean-Georges Vongerichten features a menu of French cuisine infused with tropical flavors and local ingredients.
name: Café Martinique
address: One Casino Drive Suite 4, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Located on Cable Beach, Meze Grill is a sophisticated Mediterranean restaurant offering a menu that combines seafood and meats in a refined yet relaxed atmosphere. The chic dining space features elegant decor with soft lighting, creating an intimate ambiance. The menu includes classic Mediterranean dishes such as fresh seafood, prime meats, imported pasta, and organic salads and vegetables. Guests can also enjoy a selection of fine wines from around the world, craft beers, and handcrafted cocktails.
name: Meze Grill

detail_description: Athena Cafe & Bar is a family-owned restaurant located on Bay Street since 1996. It has become a popular spot for both locals and visitors, offering Mediterranean food with Greek and Bahamian influences. The restaurant is known for its gluten-free options and is a favorite lunch spot for downtown workers and savvy cruisers. Guests can enjoy their meals on the second floor or balcony while taking in views of Nassau's downtown area.
name: Athena Cafe & Bar

detail_description: Located in Nassau, Kyma Seafood Grill is a sophisticated restaurant offering a fusion of Greek and Latin flavors. The upscale ambiance and expansive menu make it an ideal choice for various occasions, from romantic date nights to special celebrations. With chic decor and attentive service, this establishment is popular among seafood enthusiasts. Menu highlights include the crowd-pleasing gyros and the must-try grilled snapper. It's recommended to make reservations due to its popularity.
name: Kyma Seafood Grill

detail_description: Nestled just outside the upscale Lyford Cay community, Island Brothers Cie is a delightful French café and restaurant that offers an unexpected culinary experience in New Providence. This charming brasserie combines traditional French dining with tropical flair, making it a haven for food enthusiasts seeking something special. The family-run establishment serves up a delectable array of dishes, including their renowned Wagyu bavette paired with crispy pomme frites.
name: Island Brothers Cie

detail_description: Sapodilla Estate is home to the renowned fine dining establishment, Sapodilla. The restaurant offers exceptional Bahamian cuisine and top-notch service in a beautiful setting. With floor-to-ceiling windows providing stunning garden views and soothing island-style interiors, diners are treated to a feast for the senses. The chefs at Sapodilla use fresh, locally sourced ingredients to create dishes that showcase the flavors of the Bahamas.
name: Sapodilla Estate

detail_description: Nobu, the internationally renowned restaurant chain by chef Nobu Matsuhisa, has established its presence in major cities worldwide. The Atlantis location mirrors the elegance and modern design of its counterparts, offering a diverse menu featuring sushi, sashimi, steaks, tempura, and various Japanese dishes. In Nassau at Atlantis Bahamas, Nobu provides an ultra-luxe dining experience with a fusion of Japanese and Peruvian influences.
name: Nobu
address: One Casino Drive, Suite 13, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: The Poop Deck at Sandyport is a renowned seafood restaurant and bar in Nassau, serving locals and visitors since 1972. It offers Bahamian-style seafood with stunning views of Nassau Harbour from its upper deck bar. The restaurant's unobstructed views of turquoise waters make it a popular choice for dining. Guests can enjoy dishes like cracked conch, fritters, and the highly recommended conch chowder served with johnny cake.
name: The Poop Deck at Sandyport

detail_description: The New Duff is a must-visit spot, located about a 30-minute walk from the port. Despite the weather conditions, visitors found it worth the effort. The jerk chicken bun was particularly praised for its well-balanced spice and fresh veggies. The guava duff and banana duff were also highlights, with authentic fruit flavors that weren't overpowered by sweetness. Upon entering, guests were greeted by the delightful aroma of freshly baked bread.
name: The New Duff

excerpt: Relaxed, family-friendly restaurant serving a menu of homestyle Southern Italian meals.
detail_description: Carmine's is a delightful, family-friendly Italian restaurant that brings the essence of Southern Italy to life with its generous portions and warm atmosphere. Perfect for small groups, this eatery serves up hearty dishes in family-style servings, making it an ideal spot for sharing. The menu features a variety of appetizers, entrees, and desserts designed to satisfy even the hungriest diners.
name: Carmine's
address: One Casino Drive Suite 2, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Mogano by Giorgio Locatelli is a culinary gem that embraces simplicity while striving for perfection. This enchanting restaurant offers a delightful journey through the vibrant flavors of Thailand, Vietnam, and Indonesia. Guests can choose to dine in the elegant main dining room, at an intimate 8-seat sushi bar, or on the terrace with stunning waterside views that set a romantic ambiance.
name: Mogano by Giorgio Locatelli
address: Mahogany Hill Western Rd, Nassau, Bahamas

detail_description: Lukka Kairi Waterfront Bar & Grill is a vibrant seafront eatery located above Downtown Nassau's harborfront, offering a perfect spot to enjoy refreshing cocktails and innovative Bahamian cuisine. Since 2015, this modern restaurant has been serving up a mix of classic Bahamian dishes and contemporary creations.
name: Lukka Kairi Waterfront Bar & Grill

detail_description: Tiki Bikini Hut is a vibrant bar located at Junkanoo Beach, near Downtown Nassau and the cruise line docks in The Bahamas. It offers an energetic atmosphere where visitors can savor drinks and food, including the popular conch fritters. The seating extends to the beach, providing stunning views of the ocean and cruise ships.
name: Tiki Bikini Hut

detail_description: If you're looking for a seafood restaurant with some serious mounds of food, Oh Andros is the place to go. The grilled conch here is especially delicious, and the staff is always friendly and welcoming. The only downside is that it can be quite busy, so make sure to book ahead.
name: Oh Andros

detail_description: At Olives, you'll find a unique, open-cuisine that celebrates the Mediterranean cuisine. The restaurant features three meals a day and late night dining options. Casual attire is recommended.
name: Olives
address: One Casino Drive Suite 18 Paradise Island N.P, Bahamas

detail_description: Murray's Deli is a delightful destination for anyone craving authentic New York-style deli cuisine, nestled within the picturesque Atlantis Paradise Island. With breathtaking views of the Atlantis Marina, this charming eatery offers a menu brimming with beloved classics such as challah French toast and bagels topped with lox. For lunch, indulge in their Coney Island-style kosher dogs served with savory beef sauce and crispy fries.
name: Murray's Deli
address: One Casino Drive, Suite 28, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Humidor Churrascaria, located at the Graycliff Hotel in Downtown Nassau, offers a Brazilian-style dining experience. Guests can enjoy unlimited servings of expertly seasoned meats served tableside by gaucho waiters, along with a banquet-style buffet featuring an array of dishes including salads, vegetables, fresh fish, and Brazilian specialties. The restaurant's concept is inspired by the traditional Brazilian churrascaria where meats are grilled and served using large knives.
name: Humidor Churrascaria
